<div class="core-journal-description"><div property="isPartOf" typeof="Periodical"><span property="name">RadioGraphics</span></div><div class="core-enumeration"><span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationVolume">Volume <span property="volumeNumber">26</span></span> • <span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationIssue">Number <span property="issueNumber">4</span></span> • <span property="datePublished">Jul 1 2006</span></div><div class="core-pagination"><span class="heading">Pages</span>: <span class="content"><span property="pageStart">981</span> - <span property="pageEnd">992</span></span></div><div class="core-pmid"><span class="heading">PubMed</span>: <a class="content" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16844927/" property="sameAs" target="_blank" title="Link to PubMed">16844927</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-copyright"><h4>Copyright</h4><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2006.</div></section><section class="core-history"><h4>History</h4><div><b class="core-label">Published online</b>: Jul 1 2006</div></section><section class="core-permissions"><h4>Permissions</h4><div>Request permissions for this article.</div><div><a class="btn" href="https://marketplace.copyright.com/rs-ui-web/mp/search/all/10.1148%2Frg.264055082">Request Permissions</a></div></section><section property="keywords"><h4>Keywords</h4><ol><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=SE+%3D+spin+echo&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">SE = spin echo</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=3D+%3D+three-dimensional&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">3D = three-dimensional</a></li></ol></section><section class="core-article-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="paragraph">After surgery for type A aortic dissection, gadolinium-enhanced three-dimensional MR angiography is useful for evaluation of the periprosthetic area and the remaining native aorta for possible complicatio